JOHANNESBURG, October 22 –  With seven of the eight Telkom Knockout quarterfinal places already decided, the focus will shift to Durban on Tuesday when AmaZulu host Cape Town City at King Zwelithini Stadium. The 7.30pm fixture will be followed by a live quarterfinal draw. The draw will be conducted by PSL’s Luxolo September assisted by Ronnie Schloss and Braam Wessels from Telkom. The teams that have qualified so far are: (Seeded teams): Mamelodi Sundowns, Orlando Pirates, Kaizer Chiefs and Maritzburg United.
(Unseeded teams): Bidvest Wits, Baroka FC and SuperSport United. The last spot will go towards either AmaZulu or Cape Town City.  (ANA)